â€¢ Install samba-client & CIFS Utility:

yum install samba-client samba-common cifs-utils

mkdir /mnt/san

Commands:
To edit Fstab:
nano /etc/fstab

To mount Windows Share:
mount -a

To Unmount:

umount -f -a -t cifs -l san

To remove folder:

rm -rf FOLDER_NAME

Troubleshooting:

Run command df -Th

If there is any space in the server path, you need to replace it by \040, for example //servername/My\040Documents

Example:
mount -t cifs -o user=zohaib,pass=JoBHiPassword,domain=abcdef.com '//servername/Folder_Name/' /mnt/Folder_Name/
